<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910312-0119</DOCNO><DOCID>910312-0119.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- General Signal Corp.:   Manufacturer Completes Sale   Of General Railway Unit</HL><DATE>03/12/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   I.SAS GSX</CO><IN>DIVERSIFIED TECHNOLOGY (DTC)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   General Signal Corp. said it completed the sale of itsGeneral Railway Signal unit to Sasib S.p.A. of Bologna,Italy.   The sale includes General Railway's affiliates in Chinaand the Netherlands. General Signal also recently completedthe sale of its railway braking unit and a semiconductorproduct line. The company declined to disclose terms of thoseindividual transactions, but it said total proceeds for therailway signal, braking and semiconductor businesses would beabout $100 million, mostly from the General Railway sale, andwill be used to repay debt.</LP><TEXT>   General Signal, with 1990 sales of $1.69 billion, is aleading maker of equipment and process systems for theelectrical and telecommunications industries. It is based inStamford, Conn.</TEXT></DOC>